# Any of various snakes resembling a file in texture or appearence, especially a [[wart snake]] or a non-venemous South African snake of the genus ''Mehelya''.
#:*'''1988''': Peter had four barramundi and Rosie had three turtles, a possum and a fat '''file snake'''. — Tom Cole, ''Hell West and Crooked'' (Angus & Robertson 1995, p. 259)